<TEXTAREA NAME="Text" COLS="60" ROWS="6" WRAP="VIRTUAL" >GLITCH (Sonic Adventure 2 / Battle or Sonic Adventure DX Only): Reuse Animals / Chaos Drives. Place the item in front of Chao’s face without giving it to him. It will pose as if it took the item, but you can actually reuse item over and over again with this trick. Works in Sonic adventure DX too. It might be easier if you use Sonic and buy Chao heart fruit so it stays still.

The cheat below is only for Sonic adventure 2 Battle
Tip on how to get rings by cheating-
1) Buy the most expensive item, drop it off in the garden then Save
2) RETURN to the garden, take item to Black market +sell it.
As soon as it’s sold DO NOT SAVE. Hold X+B+Start in the Black market to reset game.
3) Look at your total ring count (It has increased). And if you go back to the garden the item was in, it's still there!
You can sell and reset until you have the desired amount of money!

This test will prove that feeding Chao helps them reach primary evolution faster.
Preparation:
Use 2 normal coloured Chao eggs.
Throw them at the wall so they hatch roughly at the same time, and make sure you keep both Chao in the same garden for this test+ do not let the Chao you are feeding go to sleep, because you need to feed it.
Feed one of the Chao non-stop, but leave the other + do not pet it because both Chao have to stay blue (it is best to recognise the change). You may swap sides if the one you are feeding is beginning to change alignment (i.e. baby devil / angel).
After 30 minutes or so, the Chao that you are feeding lots is becoming a darker blue and the one that you are not feeding is a lighter blue. The one that you fed lots will evolve before the one that you have not fed!
Conclusion: Feeding Chao helps them evolve faster.

This test will prove that feeding Chao helps them reach Secondary evolution faster.

You must have two freshly evolved adult Chao of the same ability. Feed one of them constantly but leave the other. You will notice that the one you are feeding is changing shape / colour faster than the one that you're not feeding.

Conclusion: Secondary evolution can speed up.

CHAO NAMES

These are official Chao names from Sonic Adventure:
Baby Chao names:
RUPICHA, RUKICHA, PUCHA, TAHCHA, TETOCHA, PITECHA, KUNCHA, PIPOCHA
Adult Chao names:
CHANNA, CHACKLE, CHAPATA, CHAHURA, CHAPUWA, CHARUKA, CHAIMA, CHASUPI
Silver Chao names: (All female Chao names)
SOPHIA, AUDREY, INGRID, ELIZA, FAYE, JULIE, JODIE, VIVIAN
Gold:
PHARAOH, SHOGUN, LORD, KING, CHAMP, GENERAL, CAESAR, EMPEROR
(Sonic team named these Gold Chao like elites)
Special Chao names:
CHACLON
Given to either:
A two-tone black child Chao (no smile, must have sleepy or normal eyes)
A two-tone black Adult Neutral Normal type Chao (no smile, normal eyes)
OMOCHAO
A blue robotic Chao that hosts the races.
CHAOTI, CHAOMA, CHAOCHA
(These are the names that appear on the high score list, on the race selection)

Sonic Adventure 2 official Chao names:
CHACRON (A two tone grey child Chao with sleepy eyes and no smile)
Jewel Chao rangers’ names:
RED, GREEN, YELLOW, BLUE, PINK

Sonic Heroes official Chao names:
CHEESE (Cream’s child Chao with a red bowtie)
CHOCOLA sibling of Cheese Chao (brown child Chao with a blue bowtie)

CHAO ABILITIES

(THIS PAGE DOES NOT INCLUDE ANY GARDEN TOYS)

ANIMAL ABILITIES

Bear= Moves forwards, shaking head side to side
Boar= Charges
Cheetah= Bathes
Condor= Does sit-ups
Dragon= Breathes fire
Gorilla= Pounds chest
Parrot= Sings
Peacock= Struts like a peacock
Penguin= Slides
Phoenix= Wags tail
Rabbit= Hops
Raccoon= Stands on tip toes making noise
Otter= Backstroke
Seal= Rolls
Sheep= Back flips
Skunk= Emits gas
Tiger= Shakes a tree (if its near)
Unicorn= Bucks feet

KINDERGARTEN LESSONS

Cymbals
Maracas
Bell
Tambourine
Drum
Trumpet
Castanets
Flute
Drawing
Song
Spin Dance
Step Dance
Go-Go Dance
Shake Dance
Exercise

CHAO RACE

Crab Pool= Shovel
Stump Valley= Watering Can
Mushroom Forest= Rattle
Block Canyon= Toy Car
Aquamarine= Sonic Doll
Topaz= Broom
Peridot= Paint Book
Garnet= Pogo Stick
Onyx= Crayons
Diamond= Bubbles</TEXTAREA></TD>

